I started looking into warhead impacts because of [Comment](https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA/pull/9357#issuecomment-159034056).
It appears that nearly all uses of warhead impacts uses the impact at position, with only `PoisonedByTiberium` and `DamagedWithoutFoundation` applying directly to actors (as well as the pending `AreaBeam`).

Long story short, in the cases that `SpreadDamageWarhead` is applied directly to actors, its `Spread` and `Range` is effectively ignored entirely.

The suggestion is that `SpreadDamageWarhead` should always use its `Spread`, and that a new warhead `DirectDamageWarhead` should be defined for cases where no spread is needed.

Hopefully this will help avoid confusion where it appears that spread is not being applied.

Search done in project for uses of warhead impact uses.

